# .dockerignore for the jaseci repo root.
#
# Used by `Dockerfile.microservice.ci` (the CI / developer-checkout
# variant of the K-track auto-build) which sets the build context to
# the repo root so it can `COPY jac /build/jac && COPY jac-scale
# /build/jac-scale` for editable installs.
#
# Without this file, the build context can balloon past 2GB (.git
# alone is ~860MB, plus per-package .jac caches add up fast). Docker
# transfers the full context to the daemon before starting any layers,
# so an oversized context times out the build before it even runs.

# === Git metadata ===
# Never needed in any image. Adds ~860MB on its own.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# === CI / GitHub metadata ===
.github

# === Editor / OS ===
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# === Python build / cache artifacts ===
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/*.egg-info
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov
**/.tox

# Virtualenvs anywhere in the tree.
**/.venv
**/venv

# Python build outputs
**/dist
**/build
*.tar.gz
*.whl

# === Jac runtime artifacts (rebuilt on first request) ===
# The .jac/ subtree mixes generated bytecode caches (large, never
# wanted in image) with user data (.jac/data, .jac/logs - also not
# wanted at build time). Excluding the whole tree is the simplest
# rule that keeps context small.
**/.jac
**/__jac_gen__

# === Frontend build artifacts ===
# node_modules is rebuilt at image build time if needed; .vite is a
# local dev cache.
**/node_modules
**/.vite
**/.next
**/.turbo

# === Out-of-git working docs (ignored via .git/info/exclude) ===
# .local-docs lives outside git on purpose; if it grew large in your
# checkout there's no reason to ship it into an image.
.local-docs

# === Local dev secrets / overrides ===
# .env can contain credentials; never bundle into image. Production
# uses K8s Secrets via env / valueFrom (P4.1 future work).
.env
.env.*
.envrc
*.local

# === Test artifacts that aren't part of source ===
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
